{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01CZAPk9nJkyYsVqPtLoGMCW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both pass.\n\n- **No header** → `stable` ✓\n- **`X-Canary: always`** → `canary` ✓\n\n## What was wrong\n\nThe canary Ingress `canary-canary` (host `canary.example.com` → `canary-echo`) had the right `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"` flag, but its matching annotations were misconfigured:\n\n- `canary-by-header: X-Feature` (should be `X-Canary`)\n- `canary-by-header-value: v2` (should be `always`)\n\nSo no request ever matched the canary condition, and everything fell through to the stable backend.\n\n## Fix\n\nUpdated the two annotations on `canary-canary`:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header=X-Canary\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value=always\n```\n\nI left the `canary-alt` Ingress alone (it's a labeled decoy: `benchmark.decoy=true`, different host `canary-alt.example.com`) and made no changes to any Deployments or Services."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":446,"cache_read_input_tokens":35126,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":446},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80698c8a-0eac-40ac-9c94-030bf333e38f","uuid":"f473f994-119e-4838-8fe6-f5ea8f07227c","request_id":"req_011CcASy7fZMQEkJMiwoLP3J"}
